    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Colossians",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Some lives are hidden with God in Christ\u2014The Saints are told to be holy and to serve the Lord Jesus Christ.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "If ye then be risen with Christ, seek those things which are above, where Christ sitteth on the right hand of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 2:12.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Set your affection on things above, not on things on the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0mind.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 6:33.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:24.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worldliness.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For ye are dead, and your life is hid with Christ in God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 6:5 (2\u20135); Col. 2:20.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When Christ, who is our life, shall appear, then shall ye also appear with him in glory.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ether 4:12.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 3:2.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 15:43 (42\u201344).",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Mortify therefore your members which are upon the earth; fornication, uncleanness, inordinate affection, evil concupiscence, and covetousness, which is idolatry:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 8:13.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 6:13.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sexual Immorality.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covet.",
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 141
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idolatry.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 160
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For which things' sake the wrath of God cometh on the children of disobedience:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Indignation of.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In the which ye also walked some time, when ye lived in them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0formerly.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But now ye also put off all these; anger, wrath, malice, blasphemy, filthy communication out of your mouth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 4:22 (22\u201324).",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Malice.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Blaspheme.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Profanity.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lie not one to another, seeing that ye have put off the old man with his deeds;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty; Lying.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 6:6; Mosiah 3:19.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And have put on the new man, which is renewed in knowledge after the image of him that created him:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 8:29.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Creator; Man, Physical Creation of.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Where there is neither Greek nor Jew, circumcision nor uncircumcision, Barbarian, Scythian, bond nor free: but Christ is all, and in all.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 12:13.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Put on therefore, as the elect of God, holy and beloved, bowels of mercies, kindness, humbleness of mind, meekness, longsuffering;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Election.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 5:22.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mercy.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Benevolence.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Humility.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meek.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Forbearing one another, and forgiving one another, if any man have a quarrel against any: even as Christ forgave you, so also do ye.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 26:31 (30\u201331).",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And above all these things put on charity, which is the bond of perfectness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Charity.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, to the which also ye are called in one body; and be ye thankful.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace of God.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Thanksgiving.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly in all wisdom; teaching and admonishing one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing with grace in your hearts to the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 32:3.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Intelligence of.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teaching.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Singing.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whatsoever ye do in word or deed, do all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God and the Father by him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 1:12. TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wives, submit yourselves unto your own husbands, as it is fit in the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Husbands, love your wives, and be not bitter against them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Husbands.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Continuing Courtship in.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Children, obey your parents in all things: for this is well pleasing unto the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Children; Family, Love within.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Duties of; Honoring Father and Mother.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1497
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Fathers, provoke not your children to anger, lest they be discouraged.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Responsibilities toward.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Provoking.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Servants, obey in all things your masters according to the flesh; not with eyeservice, as menpleasers; but in singleness of heart, fearing God:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 6:1 (1\u20132); Titus 2:9 (9\u201310); 1\u00a0Pet. 2:18.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sincere.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 120
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And whatsoever ye do, do it heartily, as to the Lord, and not unto men;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commitment; Industry; Laziness.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Knowing that of the Lord ye shall receive the reward of the inheritance: for ye serve the Lord Christ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 6:8.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Inheritance.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 7:22.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But he that doeth wrong shall receive for the wrong which he hath done: and there is no respect of persons.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Injustice.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:35; 38:16.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
